itemDescription: Governor of South Australia (1848–1854) and Tasmania (1855–1861)

wikipedia_page.main: Sir Henry Edward Fox Young, KCMG (23 April 1803 – 18 September 1870) was the fifth Governor of South Australia, serving in that role from 2 August 1848 until 20 December 1854.  He was then the first Governor of Tasmania, from 1855 until 1861.
